==English==

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|fro|pelote||small ball}}, from {{der|en|VL.|*pilotta}}, diminutive of {{der|en|la|pila||ball}}. {{doublet|en|pelota}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈpɛlɪt/}}
** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-pellet.wav |Audio (UK)}}
* {{rhymes|en|ɛlɪt}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A small, compressed, hard chunk of matter.
#: ''a '''pellet''' of wood, paper, or ore''
# A lead [[projectile]] used as ammunition in rifled air guns.
# Compressed byproduct of digestion regurgitated by owls. Serves as a waste disposal mechanism for indigestible parts of food, such as fur and bones.
# {{lb|en|heraldiccharge}} A [[roundel]] [[sable]] (black circular spot; also called [[ogress]]).
# One of the short [[conductive]] [[tube]]s in a [[Pelletron]] [[particle accelerator]].

